# Starkeep local environment.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and uncomment/edit as needed.
# `.env.local` at the repo root is the single source of truth: every consumer
# loads it — the local-data-server, the tsx CLIs, the teardown/reset shell
# scripts, and admin-web (via next.config.ts).
#
# Precedence (highest wins): an exported environment variable > .env.local > .env.
# So `STARKEEP_DIR=/path pnpm dev` still overrides whatever the file says.

# Directory where Starkeep stores ALL local state for one instance: config.json,
# data.db, app-creds/, objects/, watches.json, auth/cloud creds. Defaults to
# ~/.starkeep if unset.
#
# To run multiple, completely separate local instances (each with its own cloud
# config), point this at a different directory per instance and switch the active
# one by editing this value:
#   STARKEEP_DIR=~/.starkeep-personal
#   STARKEEP_DIR=~/.starkeep-work
# STARKEEP_DIR=~/.starkeep
